<subSubSection id="C344654D632C501C9EF4FC78CBA1FB58" pageId="5" pageNumber="468" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE136C6632C501C9EF4FC78CBA1FB58" blockId="5.[151,1437,932,1247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632C501C9EF4FC78CE6FFBE4" bold="true" box="[199,322,1004,1030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632C501C9C75FC79CD9AFBE4" authorityName="Malicky &amp; Changthong" authorityYear="2006" box="[582,695,1004,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phrixos">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632C501C9C75FC79CD9AFBE4" box="[582,695,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">P. phrixos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632C501C9DF0FC79CB82FBE5" authority="Malicky 1995" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="1995" box="[963,1199,1004,1031]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bay">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632C501C9DF0FC79CB25FBE4" box="[963,1032,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">P. bay</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632C501C9A22FC78CB82FBE5" author="Malicky" box="[1041,1199,1004,1031]" firstAuthor="Malicky" pageId="5" pageNumber="468" pagination="851 - 885" refId="ref6362" refString="Malicky, H. (1995) Neue Kocherfliegen (Trichoptera, Insecta) aus Vietnam. Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 27 (2), 851 - 885." type="journal article" year="1995">Malicky 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632C501C9ADAFC79CFE2FBC9" authority="Malicky 1995" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nam">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632C501C9ADAFC79CA1BFBE4" box="[1257,1334,1005,1030]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">P. nam</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632C501C9B0CFC78CFE2FBC9" author="Malicky" firstAuthor="Malicky" pageId="5" pageNumber="468" pagination="851 - 885" refId="ref6362" refString="Malicky, H. (1995) Neue Kocherfliegen (Trichoptera, Insecta) aus Vietnam. Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 27 (2), 851 - 885." type="journal article" year="1995">Malicky 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(both from 
<collectingCountry id="F3497656632C501C9F65FB84CE9AFBC9" box="[342,439,1040,1067]" name="Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
) in general appearance. Although 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632C501C9D04FB85CC8AFBC8" authorityName="Malicky &amp; Changthong" authorityYear="2006" box="[823,935,1040,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phrixos">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632C501C9D04FB85CC8AFBC8" box="[823,935,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">P. phrixos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
more nearly resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632C501C9A80FB85CBDAFBC8" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="1995" box="[1203,1271,1040,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bay">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632C501C9A80FB85CBDAFBC8" box="[1203,1271,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">P. bay</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is a distinct species as its preanal appendages are longer than the inferior appendages and each is more curved near the basal half in lateral view; the lateral spiniform process of each preanal appendage bears a single process. Conversely, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632C501C9B61FBCDCAB8FB90" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="1995" box="[1362,1429,1112,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bay">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632C501C9B61FBCDCAB8FB90" box="[1362,1429,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">P. bay</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the preanal appendages are shorter than the inferior appendages and not curved near their bases in lateral view; each lateral spiniform process has two branches, with the inner one being longer in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C344654D632C501C9EF4FB50CB0FFB3C" box="[199,1058,1220,1247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="468" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE136C6632C501C9EF4FB50CB0FFB3C" blockId="5.[151,1437,932,1247]" box="[199,1058,1220,1247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632C501C9EF4FB50CE4CFB3C" bold="true" box="[199,353,1220,1246]" pageId="5" pageNumber="468">Distribution.</emphasis>
